==English==  [[Image:Veldskoen.jpg.jpg|thumb|]]
===Etymology===
Afrikaans: ''vel'' hide + ''skoen'': shoe. First known usage 1731 (Dutch)[[veldschoen]].
===Noun===
'''veldskoen'''   plural '''veldskoens''' or '''veldskoene'''
#(South African) A shoe with untanned leather upper sewn without nails, similar to the Canadian [[moccasin]]. Thought to have been made by the [[Hottentot]]s before the arrival of [[European]]s, but still made and worn in South Africa.
===Reference===
'''1978''': A Dictionary of South African English. Edited Jean Branford. Oxford.
